<item>Systems are in thermal equilibrium when they have the same temperature.</item>
<item>Thermal equilibrium occurs when two bodies are in contact with each other and can freely exchange energy.</item>
<item>The zeroth law of thermodynamics states that when two systems, A and B, are in thermal equilibrium with each other, and B is in thermal equilibrium with a third system, C, then A is also in thermal equilibrium with C.</item></list></section><section id="fs-id1815795" class="conceptual-questions" type="conceptual-questions"><title>Conceptual Questions</title>
